==English==
===Etymology===
From Japanese [[大君]] (たいくん, taikun), a title for the shogun.<!-- wikipedia states "Tycoon comes from the Japanese 大君, a word borrowed from Chinese meaning "great prince" and used to imply to foreigners that the Shogun was Japan's emporer", which might have some bearing here -->

